<% @title = "Credit where credit’s due" %>

<%= render :partial => 'sidebar' %>
<div id="left_column_flip" class="left_column_flip">
<h1 id="credits"><%= @title %> <a href="#credits">#</a> </h1>

<p><%= site_name %> is a community project. It is powered by
  <a href="http://alaveteli.org/">Alaveteli</a>, open-source software for making
  access to information requests.</p>

<dl>
<dt id="development">Development <a href="#development">#</a></dt>
<dd>
 Hearty cheers to <a href="http://alaveteli.org/">Alaveteli</a>&rsquo;s many <a href="https://github.com/mysociety/alaveteli/graphs/contributors">contributors</a>.</p>
</dd>

<dt id="helpus">How to help <a href="#helpus">#</a></dt>
<dd>
  <dt id="volunteer">Become a volunteer <a href="#volunteer">#</a></dt>
  <dd>
    <p>If you have a passion for transparency, a great deal of patience, and a bit of spare time, consider helping out as a volunteer on <%= site_name %>. Work includes user support and helping resolve issues with requests, and is primarily managed via email.</p>
    <p>In the first instance, <%= link_to 'get in touch', help_contact_path %>.</p>
  </dd>

  <dt id="classification">Sort things out <a href="#classification">#</a></dt>
  <dd>
    <p>Admin can be fun! Help people find successful requests, and monitor performance of departments, by <a href="<%= categorise_play_path %>">playing the categorisation game</a>.</p>

    <p>Or be a dear, and find out request email addresses of <a href="<%= help_requesting_path(:anchor => 'missing_bodies') %>">authorities that we're missing</a>.</p>
  </dd>

  <dt id="promote">Spread the word <a href="#promote">#</a></dt>
  <dd>
    <p>We don’t have a marketing budget, so word of mouth really helps.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Write a blog post about <%= site_name %>, or an interesting request that you've found.</li>
        <li>Post about the site, and what you can do with it, on a forum that you frequent.</li>
        <li>Tell friends about it.</li>
        <li>Let your local newspaper or community publication know how useful we are.</li>
        <li>Give a talk.</li>
      </ul>
  </dd>
</dd>

  <dt id="code">Improve our code <a href="#code">#</a></dt>
  <dd>
    <p>Seen something that could work better? If you're a programmer, <a href="https://github.com/mysociety/alaveteli/">get the source code</a> for the upstream project, <a href="http://alaveteli.org/">Alaveteli</a>, and send a pull request. <%= site_name %> is coded in <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Ruby on Rails</a>.</p>
  </dd>
</dl>

<div id="hash_link_padding"></div>

</div>
